I found that data window is rather versatile tool and its data source can be 
even come from RDBMS stored procedure. I don't think FP can do this. 

One of the beauties of datawindow is that it *knows* how to generate SQL 
statements, according to the row status flags, when you issue Update() method. 
In FP you have to figure it out. And the programmer can tell the datawindow 
how to generate SQL statements by changing the row status as well. 

